snippet.textDisplay: Those people in Kramatorsk, who disobeyed orders in the beginning of Russian Invasion to destroy advanced 155mm Ukrainian howitzer and handed over it to Ukrainian Army instead, did a good job for their country. The same did those people in Kyiv who disobeyed orders and handed over Ukrainian Stugna-P anti-tank weapons to Ukrainian Army instead of exporting them to Arab countries, although they were already paid off in advance. Bad job was done by those people who obeyed orders and removed mine fields from border between Crimea and Kherson District during December-February 2022, despite of US Intelligence report of imminent Russian Invasion. That's why Russian tactical group O from Crimea reached Mariupol in just 4 days after Invasion.
